**Image-generating deep learning model**

## DALL-E

*Watermark present on DALL-E images*

One might observe an image generated by DALL-E 2, a peculiar artifact born from the prompt "Teddy bears working on new AI research underwater with 1990s technology." A testament, perhaps, to the sheer whimsicality that humanity often demands from its machines, or simply a demonstration of what happens when you let algorithms loose on the collective unconscious.

This particular digital entity, DALL-E, is not a singular creation but rather a lineage of [text-to-image models](/Text-to-image_model), meticulously crafted and unleashed upon the world by the ever-prolific minds at [OpenAI](/OpenAI). These models leverage the formidable, if somewhat overhyped, power of [deep learning](/Deep_learning) methodologies to conjure [digital images](/Digital_image) from mere textual descriptions—what the industry, in its infinite creativity, has dubbed "prompts."

The initial iteration of DALL-E first made its rather quiet debut on 5&#160;January 2021, a mere four years ago, or an eternity in the frantic pace of technological "progress." Its [stable release](/Software_release_life_cycle) for the latest incarnation, DALL-E 3, arrived more recently on 10&#160;August 2023. The platform, as one might expect from such endeavors, is entrenched in [Cloud computing platforms](/Cloud_computing_platforms), ensuring its omnipresence and accessibility. DALL-E is, in essence, a [Text-to-image model](/Text-to-image_model), a specialized [type](/Software_categories) of software operating under a [Proprietary](/Proprietary_software) [service](/Software_as_a_service) license. Its ultimate successor, or perhaps its replacement, appears to be [GPT Image](/GPT_Image), suggesting a perpetual cycle of iteration and obsolescence.

This entire exercise is, of course, merely a facet of a larger, ongoing saga, intricately woven into [a series](/Category:Artificial_intelligence) dedicated to the grand, often bewildering, domain of [Artificial intelligence (AI)](/Artificial_intelligence).

